  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: NA\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10 64-bit\r\nCommit hash : NA\r\n\r\nIn the \"Installation instructions for Windows\" Wiki page located at: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Installation-instructions-for-Windows\r\n\r\nThere is a line of instructions with the following setx command:\r\nC:\\Users\\xxx> setx Path \"%Path%\"\r\n\r\nOn my system, this resulted in the following warning message: \r\nWARNING: The data being saved is truncated to 1024 characters.\r\n\r\nUpon checking my Environment variables using the Windows GUI and the registry, as well as by typing \"path\" at the command prompt, I can see that the path does indeed appear to be truncated as it ends in the middle of a directory name.\r\n\r\nThis web site shows a solution to recovering from this problem: \r\nhttps://superuser.com/questions/812754/how-to-recover-from-path-being-truncated-to-1024-characters-by-setx\r\n\r\nNeedless to say, this kind of data loss could mess up a system if the user is not paying attention.\r\n\r\nThere may be a switch for setx to get around the 1024 limitation, I will get back here if I find a solution.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, I believe the instructions should note this to prevent damage.\r\n",
